	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One bad thing about SNES sound is that developers were way too careful to avoid clamping higher frequencies, so much so that you can easily double audio without ever clamping anything in most games.
<br />
<br />Of course that's just a "turn the volume up on the TV" thing, more annoying with emulators when all your other audio apps play five times louder.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
